  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "hackernews",
      "subsource": "news.ycombinator.com",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "I built a vulnerable app and spent $1,500 seeing if LLMs could hack it",
      "url": "https://kasra.blog/blog/i-spent-1500-seeing-if-llms-could-hack-my-app/",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48392343",
      "score": 356,
      "comments": 191,
      "author": "jc4p",
      "published": "2026-06-04T00:56:32Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Testing LLM agents (like GPT-4) against a custom vulnerable app cost $1,500, revealing high API consumption for autonomous exploitation.",
        "LLMs successfully solved basic web vulnerabilities (SQLi, XSS) but struggled heavily with complex, multi-step logical chains and state tracking.",
        "Current LLM agent architectures remain inefficient for pentesting, hampered by context window limitations and high rates of logical hallucination."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "Reproducible Builds in May 2026",
      "url": "https://reproducible-builds.org/reports/2026-05/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/cubjpv",
      "score": 2,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "fanf",
      "published": "2026-06-04T19:47:34Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Achieving bit-for-bit identical binaries requires eliminating non-deterministic elements like local timestamps, CPU instructions, and absolute build paths from toolchains.",
        "Toolchains like Nix, Guix, and modern Go/Rust compilers natively support hermetic builds to ensure predictable cryptographic hashes for target artifacts.",
        "Deterministic builds secure the software supply chain, aligning CI/CD pipelines with SLSA Level 3/4 and SBOM standards like SPDX."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Pwnd Blaster: Hacking your PC using your speaker without ever touching it",
      "url": "https://blog.nns.ee/2026/06/03/katana-badusb/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/mth4mj",
      "score": 48,
      "comments": 5,
      "author": "matthew2",
      "published": "2026-06-03T11:54:11Z",
      "bullets": [
        "This attack vector leverages PC speakers for acoustic or ultrasonic injection, potentially exploiting mic-to-speaker hardware loops to execute unauthorized commands.",
        "Security teams must assess threat models for acoustic side-channels, ensuring unused audio input devices are disabled at the OS level.",
        "Air-gapped systems remain vulnerable to RF, electromagnetic, or acoustic leakage emitted directly from standard computer speakers."
      ]
    },
